      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix getSubagentDepth for legacy subagent session keys (AI-assisted)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes a silent bug where `getSubagentDepth()` returned `0` for legacy subagent session keys (e.g. `subagent:worker`) because the old implementation only split on `:subagent:` (requiring a colon on both sides), missing keys that start directly with `subagent:`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Replace `raw.split(\":subagent:\")` with `normalized.match(/(^|:)subagent:/g)` in `getSubagentDepth()`\n- Normalize key via `parseAgentSessionKey` for consistent handling\n- Add test cases for legacy key formats\n\n## Test Plan\n\n- [x] New test cases pass: `subagent:worker → depth 1`, `subagent:parent:subagent:child → depth 2`\n- [x] Existing test cases unchanged\n- [x] CI: check-lint pass, dependency-guard pass\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: `getSubagentDepth()` failed to detect legacy subagent session keys. Keys like `subagent:worker` (starting directly with `subagent:` without a preceding colon) returned depth 0 instead of 1. This happened because `raw.split(':subagent:')` requires colons on both sides of `subagent:`.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Production OpenClaw instance (v2026.6.1, Node.js v22, Linux) with real subagent workflows. Also verified in Node.js REPL on main branch.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**: \n\n1. Started OpenClaw gateway with this branch applied\n2. Triggered a subagent session that creates a legacy session key `subagent:worker`\n3. Verified `getSubagentDepth(\"subagent:worker\")` returned 1 (previously 0)\n4. Verified nested legacy key `subagent:parent:subagent:child` returned 2\n\nNode.js REPL confirmation:\n```js\nconst { getSubagentDepth } = require('./src/sessions/session-key-utils');\nconsole.log(getSubagentDepth('subagent:worker'));           // 1 (was 0)\nconsole.log(getSubagentDepth('subagent:parent:subagent:child')); // 2 (was 1)\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n```\n$ node -e \"\nconst { getSubagentDepth } = require('./src/sessions/session-key-utils');\nconsole.log('legacy:', getSubagentDepth('subagent:worker'));\nconsole.log('legacy nested:', getSubagentDepth('subagent:parent:subagent:child'));\nconsole.log('standard:', getSubagentDepth('agent:main:subagent:parent:subagent:child'));\n\"\nlegacy: 1\nlegacy nested: 2\nstandard: 2\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: \n\n- Legacy key `subagent:worker` correctly returns depth 1 (was 0)\n- Nested legacy key `subagent:parent:subagent:child` correctly returns depth 2 (was 1)\n- Standard key `agent:main:subagent:parent:subagent:child` unchanged at depth 2\n- All existing test cases pass without modification\n\n**Not tested**: None for the behavior changed by this PR. Broader unrelated gateway/typecheck failures on current main are outside this PR scope.\n",
        "branch": "bughunt/fix-subagent-depth-legacy-key",
